caption: This place is so good

I absolutely love this juice generation. The staff are great, they put together great smoothies and juices, the ingredients are high quality and fresher than I've ever seen any juice place have. This means a lot because during this corona virus thing I've seen a lot of businesses scale down on quality but juice generation has stayed true to this lol to the point where I'm writing a review. Thank you for holding it down with wonderful quality products!!!

(Translated by Google) I would give this place five stars if not for its exaggerated prices. The combinations and the flavor of the excellent juices, as well as the hygiene and the service, but I think its prices are an exaggeration. A 12-ounce juice costs between $ 7 and $ 9. And the shakes $ 9 USD. 20 oz. These prices will seem insignificant for those with excellent financial solvency, but not for those with a minimum wage. I was visiting from from Florida and so many of my friends from New York kept telling me to try this juice bar. So of course I went to see what all the hype was. As soon as I walked in I was greeted energetically by a guy with glasses. I haven't even ordered yet and I felt so welcomed. I ordered a recommended drink from one of the employees, which was really amazing. It was a joyful almond with peanut butter, strawberries, blueberries and spinach. I would really recommend anyone to step into juice generation Brooklyn location, not only do they have amazing employees but a really nice and clean store and great customer service.

Juice Generation is a great chain. They have awesome juice options for everyone. They also have a whole section of vegan pastries, which is great. We had the kale, bananas, mango smoothie which hit the spot. The vegan muffins are also pretty delicious, we had the almond one and we liked it a lot.

I go here all the time to get smoothies and they usually do a great job. I bought some of the spirulina popcorn which I get from time to time. I opened it and tried it and it had clearly gone bad despite not being pass the expiration date. I spoke to an employee named David later to either return it or get something off my next purchase and he refused. I suggested that they check with their supplier but I felt as though he didn't believe me or care that I was a regular. They need to have better customer service protocols. Making my own smoothies at home rather than supporting a business that doesn't acknowledge its community ✌️
